<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16 pt-14">
  <p class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ppq-red">Listen anywhere</p>
  <h1 class="mt-3 max-w-4xl font-display text-4xl uppercase leading-tight md:text-5xl">One brand, multiple listening channels</h1>
  <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-ppq-muted">
    Pop Punk Queso should follow you everywhere.
    Pick your platform, save the playlist, and keep it in regular rotation.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16">
  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <article class="goop-panel p-6 md:p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl uppercase">Listen on your platform</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-ppq-muted">
        Open Pop Punk Queso where you already listen and keep it pinned in your library.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4">
        <%= render "shared/platform_buttons", stacked: true %>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="goop-panel p-6 md:p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl uppercase">Smart platform chooser</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-ppq-muted">Quickly pick where you listen today. This can be expanded into tracked smart-links later.</p>
      <div
        class="mt-4"
        data-vue-component="PlatformSelector"
        data-platforms='<%= {
          spotify: platform_urls[:spotify],
          apple_music: platform_urls[:apple_music],
        }.to_json %>'
      ></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16">
  <div class="goop-panel p-6 md:p-8">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl uppercase">Why follow and save?</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 grid gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-ppq-muted md:grid-cols-3">
      <li class="rounded-xl bg-ppq-paper p-4">You get regular adds, not dormant playlist graveyard energy.</li>
      <li class="rounded-xl bg-ppq-paper p-4">Every rotation is curated for replay, not trend-chasing.</li>
      <li class="rounded-xl bg-ppq-paper p-4">You can follow the same brand voice across updates, articles, and future drops.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16">
  <%= render "shared/email_signup", source: "listen" %>
</section>
